theorem Topology.dense_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : Dense (A : Set X)) : Topology.P3 (X:=X) A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x _
  -- The closure of a dense set is the entire space.
  have h_cl : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hA.closure_eq
  -- Consequently, its interior is also the entire space.
  have : (x : X) âˆˆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    simpa [h_cl, interior_univ]
  exact this

theorem Topology.interior_closure_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    interior (closure (Set.univ : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  simpa [closure_univ, interior_univ]
